KEIL µVISION PROJECT SETUP
1. Create New Project:
Open Keil µVision5

Project → New µVision Project

Select AT89S52 from device database

Create project folder structure

2. Configuration Settings:
c
// Target Options Configuration:
- Device: AT89S52
- Xtal (MHz): 11.0592
- Use On-chip ROM (0x0-0xFFF)
- Memory Model: Small
- Code Rom Size: Large
- Operating System: None
3. Build Configuration:
bash
# Build Process:
1. Add source files to project
2. Set include paths
3. Configure output for HEX file generation
4. Build target (F7)
5. Verify no errors/warnings
FLASH MAGIC PROGRAMMING STEPS
1. Hardware Connection:
text
8051 Board → USB to UART Converter
P3.0 (RX)  → TX of USB-UART
P3.1 (TX)  → RX of USB-UART
VCC (5V)   → 5V
GND        → GND
2. Programming Procedure:
Connect hardware as per circuit diagram

Open Flash Magic software

Select correct COM port

Choose device: AT89S52

Set interface: ISP

Load HEX file from Keil output

Click "Start" to program

Verify successful programming

CIRCUIT DIAGRAM (Proteus)
Components List:
text
Microcontroller: AT89S52
Crystal: 11.0592 MHz
Capacitors: 2x 33pF, 10µF electrolytic
Resistors: 8x 330Ω, 4x 10kΩ
LEDs: 8x (Red/Green)
Buttons: 4x tactile switches
Power: 5V DC supply
Connectors: USB to UART interface
Schematic Connections:
text
P1.0-P1.7 → LEDs through 330Ω resistors
P0.0-P0.3 → Buttons with pull-up resistors (10kΩ)
P3.0 → RX of USB-UART
P3.1 → TX of USB-UART
XTAL1 → 11.0592 MHz crystal
XTAL2 → Crystal with capacitors
RESET → 10kΩ pull-up with 10µF capacitor
VCC → 5V
GND → Ground
